      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Charles Staley and another\nhunter from Spokane had their\nguns taken from them while they\nwere hunting on the Colville reser-\nwalton. The farmer who turned\nthe trick informed the men that he\nwas acting on instructions from In\ndian Agent Webster. The farmers\nhouse was well enough stocked\nwith guns to indicate that he had\nbeen doing a big business in con-\nfiscation. Staley is minus a $50\nrepeating shotgun, and wonders if\npit was taken from him legally."
    }
  ]
